HEADWORD: Eupnæa
<hw>Eup*n⟦ae⟧"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. gr.
<?/ easy breathing; <grk>e'y^</grk> well + <?/ to breathe.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Normal breathing where arterialization of the
blood is normal, in distinction from <contr>dyspn⟦ae⟧a</contr>, in which
the blood is insufficiently arterialized.</def>
<rj><au>Foster.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
